&gt; if (typeof(Storage) !== &quot;undefined&quot;) {

This line of code is used to check whether the browser support LocalStorage or not.

With reference to [this article](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/localStorage), we can see that the LocalStorage support IE 8+ and Microsoft Edge 12+. You could check your browser version and make sure it support localStorage.

I have created a sample using the following code:

    &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;select id=&quot;mySelect&quot;&gt;
            &lt;option value=&quot;us&quot;&gt;us&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value=&quot;de&quot;&gt;de&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value=&quot;en&quot;&gt;en&lt;/option&gt;
        &lt;/select&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
        var lang;
        function translateTexts() {

            if (typeof (Storage) !== &quot;undefined&quot;) {
                if (window.localStorage.getItem(&quot;lang&quot;) == null) {
                    window.localStorage.setItem(&quot;lang&quot;, &#39;de&#39;);
                }

                var lang = window.localStorage.getItem(&quot;lang&quot;);
                debugger;
                if (lang == &#39;de&#39;) {
                    document.getElementById(&quot;mySelect&quot;).selectedIndex = &quot;1&quot;;
                }
                if (lang == &#39;en&#39;) {
                    document.getElementById(&quot;mySelect&quot;).selectedIndex = &quot;2&quot;;
                }
                console.log(&quot;support storage&quot;);
            } else {
                lang = &quot;de&quot;;
                console.log(&quot;de&quot;);
            }

        }

        translateTexts();
    &lt;/script&gt;

It code works well on my side (using Microsoft Edge 44.18362.1.0 and IE 11.116.18362.0 version),  and the result like this.[![enter image description here][1]][1]

So, please check your javascript code, whether there have another script will cause this issue. 

Besides, You could try to clear the browser cache, history and the browser data, then re-test your code (also you could create a new sample to test above code).
